00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Facts of migrants in Germany.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Immigration plays an important role in Germany.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Every fourth citizen has a migration background.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:20,000
That means at least one part of the population is of foreign origin.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Where is Germany in the world's comparison?

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:34,000
On second place. But the USA leads classic immigration countries like Canada, Australia and Switzerland are behind Germany.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Are most of the immigrants refugees?

8
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:44,000
No, most of them came in 2018 from Romania, Poland and Bulgaria.

9
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:49,000
The main motive of all immigrants is to look for work.

10
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Do they all find a job? No.

11
00:00:53,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Almost half of the 2.3 million unemployed people have a migration background.

12
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Their unemployment rate is twice as high.

13
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,000
What is the reason?

14
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,000
The most common reason is lack of language skills.

15
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Another reason is discrimination.

16
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Especially Turkish and Arabic names have a negative effect on applications.

17
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:27,000
With the same qualification and German name, the chances of finding a job are much higher, according to studies.

18
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:31,000
Are the migrants welcome in Germany? Yes and no.

19
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:36,000
52% of Germans think there are too many immigrants.

20
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:42,000
65% think there is a positive effect on the economy.

21
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Is the German concept of migration background problematic?

22
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Yes, only from the third generation, immigrants become officially German.

23
00:01:52,000 --> 00:02:17,000
In countries like Great Britain and Poland, the migrant stamp has disappeared after one generation.

